Trinexapac-ethyl Rate Response R Script
attributes.description: The R script is from an experiments regarding the response of bermudagrass off-types and cultivars to increasing rates of trinexapac-ethyl.  The response variable is clipping weight expressed as mg per square cm.  The experiment was a completely randomized design with grass sample and trinexapac-ethyl rate in a factorial treatment arrangement.  Time after treatment was included in the analysis as a repeated measure.  There are also three replications per treatment and two experimental replicates that were combined to create an additive blocking factor in the analysis.  A linear mixed model was fit onto the data and then an analysis of variance was performed on each factor in the model.  Post-hob pairwise comparisons were performed on significant factors to determine differences among treatments.

attributes.title: Trinexapac-ethyl Rate Response Data
attributes.description: The data presented is from an experiment evaluating the response of bermudagrass off-types and cultivars to increasing rates of the plant growth regulator, trinexapac-ethyl.  Rates included 0, 1.6, 3.3, 6.6, 13.1, 26.3, 52.6, or 105.2 g active ingredient per hectare.  Grass samples included three, morphologically distinct off-type grasses and bermudagrass cultivars Champion, MiniVerde, and TifEagle.  The response variable is clipping weight expressed as mg per square cm.  The experiment was a completely randomized design with grass sample and trinexapac-ethyl rate in a factorial treatment arrangement.  Clippings were harvested 7, 14, 21, and 28 days after treatment and was included in the analysis as a repeated measure.

attributes.title: Nitrogen Rate Response Data
attributes.description: The data presented is from an experiment evaluating the response of bermudagrass off-types and cultivars to increasing rates of nitrogen fertilizer.  Rates included 0, 6, 12, 18, 24, or 48 kg nitrogen per hectare per week for four consecutive weeks.  Grass samples included three, morphologically distinct off-type grasses and bermudagrass cultivars Champion, MiniVerde, and TifEagle.  The response variable is clipping weight expressed as mg per square cm.  The experiment was a completely randomized design with grass sample and nitrogen rate in a factorial treatment arrangement.  Clippings were harvested 7, 14, 21, and 28 days after treatment and was included in the analysis as a repeated measure.
